Screeplot, CummulativePlot, PC1/PC2 Plot

screeplot(data_pca.pca, type = "l", npcs = 15, main = "Screeplot of the first 10 PCs")

cumpro <- cumsum(data_pca.pca$sdev^2 / sum(data_pca.pca$sdev^2))
plot(cumpro[0:15], xlab = "PC #", ylab = "Amount of explained variance", main = "Cumulative variance plot")

plot(data_pca.pca$x[,1],data_pca.pca$x[,2], xlab="PC1 (65.5%%)", ylab = "PC2 (8.6%)", main = "PC1 / PC2 - plot")

library(datasets)
data(iris)
summary(iris)

##  1st Qu.:5.100   1st Qu.:2.800   1st Qu.:1.600   1st Qu.:0.300  
##  Median :5.800   Median :3.000   Median :4.350   Median :1.300  
##  Mean   :5.843   Mean   :3.057   Mean   :3.758   Mean   :1.199  
##  3rd Qu.:6.400   3rd Qu.:3.300   3rd Qu.:5.100   3rd Qu.:1.800  
##  Max.   :7.900   Max.   :4.400   Max.   :6.900   Max.   :2.500  
##        Species  
##  setosa    :50  
##  versicolor:50  
##  virginica :50  
##                 
##                 
## 
train <- sample(1:150, 100)
r3 <- lda(Species ~ ., # training model
          iris, 
          prior = c(1,1,1)/3, 
          subset = train)
plda = predict(object = r3, # predictions
               newdata = iris[-train, ])
head(plda$class) # classification result

## Levels: setosa versicolor virginica
